description: Russia-Ukraine war news LIVE Updates March 4: The Zaporizhzhia nuclear power plant in Ukraine, the largest of its kind in Europe, was on fire early on Friday after an attack by Russian troops, the mayor of the nearby town of Energodar said. As heavy fighting and shelling continues in parts of Ukraine, Russian and Ukrainian delegations met for the second round of talks in Brest on Thursday to discuss the Russian invasion. Meanwhile, Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said if Ukraine falls to Russian forces, the Baltic States could be next. He also said that "direct talks" with Russian President Vladimir Putin are the "only way" to end the war. Russia declared a full-scale invasion of Ukraine on February 24, displacing over 1 million people in a week. Stay tuned to Indiatoday.in for latest updates on the Russia-Ukraine war.
